<Group labelreference="L2" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">restart; with(plots): with(LinearAlgebra):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L3" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">the equations for the real pendulum....</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L4" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">twopi := evalf(2*Pi);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L5" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f1 := (x, y, z) -&gt; y:</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f2 := (x, y, z) -&gt; -beta * y - twopi * (Omega^2 - alpha * sin(z)) * sin(twopi*x):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f3 := (x, y, z) -&gt; twopi:</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE1 := diff(x(t), t) = f1(x(t), y(t), z(t)):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE2 := diff(y(t), t) = f2(x(t), y(t), z(t)):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE3 := diff(z(t), t) = f3(x(t), y(t), z(t)):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sys := DE1, DE2, DE3;</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">ic := x(0) = 0.1, y(0) = 0, z(0) = 0;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L6" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">the linearization around the unstable fixed point results in a Mathieu equation....</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L7" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">g1 := (x, y, z) -&gt; y:</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">g2 := (x, y, z) -&gt; -beta * y - twopi^2 * (- Omega^2 + alpha * sin(z)) * x;
g3 := (x, y, z) -&gt; twopi:</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE12 := diff(x(t), t) = g1(x(t), y(t), z(t)):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE22 := diff(y(t), t) = g2(x(t), y(t), z(t)):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE32 := diff(z(t), t) = g3(x(t), y(t), z(t)):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sys2 := DE12, DE22, DE32;</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">ic2 := x(0) = 0.01, y(0) = 0, z(0) = 0;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L8" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">Omega := 0.1;</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">beta := evalf(twopi*0.2*Omega);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">alpha0 := evalf(sqrt(2*Omega^2 * ((twopi^2 + Omega^2)^2 + (twopi * beta)^2) / (twopi^2 + Omega^2)^2));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L9" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">alpha := 0.36;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L10" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">t0 := 0; t1 := 300; N := (t1-t0);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">tt := Array(1..N, i-&gt; evalf(i/N) * (t1 - t0));</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" linebreak="space" spaceabove="0" rightmargin="0" bullet="none" firstindent="0" linespacing="0.0" pagebreak-before="false" leftmargin="0" alignment="left" initial="0" spacebelow="0">sol_arr := dsolve({sys,ic},[x(t),y(t),z(t)],type=numeric,maxfun=-1,output=tt):</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" linebreak="space" spaceabove="0" rightmargin="0" bullet="none" firstindent="0" linespacing="0.0" pagebreak-before="false" leftmargin="0" alignment="left" initial="0" spacebelow="0">soldd:=sol_arr[2,1];</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" linebreak="space" spaceabove="0" rightmargin="0" bullet="none" firstindent="0" linespacing="0.0" pagebreak-before="false" leftmargin="0" alignment="left" initial="0" spacebelow="0">xx := soldd[1..N, 2]:</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" linebreak="space" spaceabove="0" rightmargin="0" bullet="none" firstindent="0" linespacing="0.0" pagebreak-before="false" leftmargin="0" alignment="left" initial="0" spacebelow="0">yy := soldd[1..N, 3]:</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" linebreak="space" spaceabove="0" rightmargin="0" bullet="none" firstindent="0" linespacing="0.0" pagebreak-before="false" leftmargin="0" alignment="left" initial="0" spacebelow="0">zz := soldd[1..N, 4]:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L11" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">pp := seq([tt[i], xx[i]], i=1..N):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">pointplot([pp]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L12" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">An analysis of the stability of the solution...</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L13" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">restart; with(plots):with(LinearAlgebra):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L14" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de := diff(theta(t), t, t) +beta * diff(theta(t), t) + (Omega^2 - alpha * sin(t)) * sin(theta(t)) = 0;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L15" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sin(a*t+eps*sin(omega*t+phi))=convert(taylor(sin(a*t+eps*sin(omega*t+phi)), eps, 2), polynom);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L16" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">eval(subs(theta(t) =  a*t+eps*sin(omega*t+phi), de));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L17" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">subs(%%, %);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L18" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">expand(%);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L19" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Now we assume that the reaction of the pendulum is much slower than that of the vibration so we can decompose in a fast and a slow part...</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L20" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">theta(t) := ts(t)+tf(t);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L21" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L22" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">We assume that the fast part has a small amplitude, so that we can simplify the combined sine term as:</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L23" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sin(a+b) = convert(taylor(expand(sin(a+b), trig), b=0, 2), polynom);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sol := subs({a=ts(t), b=tf(t)}, %);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L24" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de_decomp := subs(sol, de);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L25" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de_slow := diff(ts(t), t$2) + beta*diff(ts(t), t)+(Omega^2*(sin(ts(t))) -alpha * av(sin(t)*tf(t))*cos(ts(t))) = 0;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L26" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de_fast := simplify(de_decomp - de_slow);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L27" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">We assume that the term  sin(t)*tf(t) - av(sin(t)*tf(t)) ~ 0. Note that if you substitute theta_f=sin(t), you see that is a forcing at the double frequency but with half the amplitude.</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L28" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de_fast:=eval(algsubs(av(sin(t)*tf(t))=sin(t)*tf(t), de_fast));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L29" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Note that this is an equation of the form:</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L30" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de_form := diff(tf(t), t$2) + a * diff(tf(t), t) + b * tf(t) = c * sin(t);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L31" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">With solution:</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L32" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sol_tf := dsolve(de_form, tf(t));</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">_C1 := 0; _C2 := 0;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L33" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sol_tf;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L34" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">timav := f -&gt; 1/(2*Pi) * int(f, t=0..2*Pi);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L35" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">sol_tf*sin(t);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">av_nl := av(lhs(%)) = timav(rhs(%));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L36" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" linebreak="space" spaceabove="0" rightmargin="0" bullet="none" firstindent="0" linespacing="0.0" pagebreak-before="false" leftmargin="0" alignment="left" initial="0" spacebelow="0">a := beta; b := Omega^2*cos(ts(t)); c := alpha*sin(ts(t));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L37" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Check if these coefficients are correct...</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L38" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">simplify(de_fast - de_form);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">simplify(lhs(%) - rhs(%));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L39" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">They are. Substituting the correlation between forcing and tf into the equation of the slow dynamics results in a non-linear but autonomous system of equations:</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L40" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">subs(av_nl, de_slow);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L41" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">de_slow := collect(%, sin(ts(t)));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L42" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">... Alternatively one could use the doubling rule to get an expression like</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L43" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">algsubs(alpha^2*sin(ts(t)) = alpha^2 / 2 / cos(ts(t)) * sin(2 * ts(t)), %%):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L44" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">collect(de_slow, [sin(ts(t))]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L45" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">k := simplify(op(1,op(1, lhs(%))));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L46" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f := (x, y) -&gt; y; g := (x, y) -&gt; -beta * y - subs(ts(t)=x, k) * sin(x);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L47" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">J := VectorCalculus:-Jacobian([f(x,y), g(x,y)], [x, y]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L48" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">beta := 'beta'; </Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">subs({x=0, y=0}, J);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L49" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">ev := simplify(Eigenvalues(%));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L50" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">algsubs(Omega^2 = Omega2, ev):</Text-field>
</Input>
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">alpha_min_stable := solve(%[2], alpha);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L51" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">beta := 0.3; Omega := 1.2; </Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L52" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">evalf(ev);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L53" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot([Re(ev[1]), Re(ev[2])], alpha=0..1.5);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L54" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot({alpha_min_stable}, Omega2=-1..3, view=[-1..3, -2..2]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L55" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Stability diagram based on the sign of the 'spring constant'.</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Blue is unstable, white is stable.</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Negative Omega^2 seem physically impossible, but these can be used to have the stability of the normal (Omega^2&gt;0) and the inverted state (Omega^2) in one graph. It will be shown below that this is a good assumption.</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L56" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">alpha := 'alpha'; Omega := 'Omega'; beta := 0.2;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L57" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">k2 := algsubs(Omega^2=Omega2, subs(cos(ts(t))=1, k));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L58" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plotsetup(ps, plotoutput=`app_invpend_stability.eps`, plotoptions=`portrait,noborder,width=8cm,height=4cm`);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L59" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">contourplot(k2, Omega2=-1..3, alpha=0..2 ,contours=[0], filled=true, numpoints=3000, coloring=[grey, white], labels=[&quot;W&quot;, &quot;a&quot;], font=[SYMBOL, 6]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
